h3. Problem Definition
LDAP synchronization will fail there is a group in LDAP that has no 'Group Name Attribute' configured and this blocks the entire synchronization process.

Example scenario:
{quote}
JIRA is configured to Microsoft Active Directory and the "Group Name Attribute" is set to use "displayName" attribute since the "CN" attribute configured for the Distribution Lists are not so familiar for the end users.
When a group without "displayName" attribute was added to the Distribution Lists, sync fails.
{quote}

h3. Suggested Solution
Implement a "fallback" 'Group Name Attribute' to prevent blocked full synchronization.

