h3. When using the Project Import tool if a text field's length exceeds the target JIRA's maximum length, validation fails with an error like {{The largest text field with length XXXX exceeds the allowed limit of YYYY.  Increase the limit in advanced settings to continue.}}

One example of where this could occur is merging two independent JIRA instances due to a corporate merger. 

h3. Instead of requiring that the text field limit be increased for the entire JIRA instance, identify in the logs or in the error message which Issue or Field is exceeding the limit so that corrective action can be taken in the originating JIRA instance. 
 
h3. Workaround 
This validation checks the maximum length of "issue description, environment, comment or text custom fields" so it is possible to directly query the originating JIRA's database in the {{jiraissue}}, {{jiraaction}}, and {{customfieldvalue}} tables for over-long entries

